The Energy Department has also announced that diesel will go up by 33.16 cents and paraffin will increase by 8 cents. JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Energy has announced that the petrol price will increase at midnight by 9 cents per litre. Diesel will go up by 33.16 cents and paraffin will increase by 8 cents. Department of Energy spokesperson Robert Maake said the main reason for the adjustment was the inclusion of a carbon tax levy in the price of both petrol and diesel of 10 cents and 9 cents [respectively] a litre. The levy was announced by the minister of finance in February. "Number two: the oil price increased slightly during the period under review compared to the previous period,‚Äù Maake said. 